A comic book style illustration of a frustrated software developer sitting at a desk, staring at a computer monitor displaying a progress bar stuck at 99%, while behind them through a window the seasons visibly change from summer to autumn to winter to spring. The developer's coffee mug has grown cold with cobwebs, their beard has grown impossibly long, and a small plant on the desk has evolved into a towering vine. Bold dynamic lines and halftone dot patterns emphasize the absurdity, with dramatic speed lines radiating from the frozen progress bar. The color palette features punchy primary colors with heavy black outlines typical of classic comic art.
